obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (34771)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34771&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Ancient Monuments Preservation`
  line `Act, 1904.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2`
  line `[except the State of Jammu and Kashmir].]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `2. Subs by the A.O. 1950, for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "except Part B States"`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34772)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34772&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(1) "ancient monument" means any structure, erection or monument or any tumulus or place of`
  line `interment, or any cave, rock-sculpture, inscription or monolith, which is of historical, archeological or`
  line `artistic interest, or any remains thereof, and includes--`
  line
  line `(a) the site of an ancient monument;`
  line
  line `(b) such portion of land adjoining the site of an ancient monument as may be required for fencing`
  line `or covering in or otherwise preserving such monument; and`
  line
  line `(c) the means of access to and convenient inspection of an ancient monument:`
  line
  line `(2) "antiquities" include any moveable objects which ^1[the Central Government], by reason of their`
  line `historical or archeological associations, may think it necessary to protect against injury, removal or`
  line `dispersion:`
  line
  line `(3) "Commissioner" includes any officer authorised by ^2[the Central Government] to perform the`
  line `duties of a Commissioner under this Act:`
  line
  line `(4) "maintain" and "maintenance" include the fencing, covering in, repairing, restoring and cleansing`
  line `of a protected monument, and the (doing of any act which may be necessary for the purpose of`
  line `maintaining a protected monument or of securing convenient access thereto:`
  line
  line `(5) "land" includes a revenue-free estate, a revenue-paying estate, and a permanent transferable`
  line `tenure, whether such estate or tenure be subject to incumbrances or not: and`
  line
  line `(6) "owner" includes a joint owner invested with powers of management on behalf of himself and`
  line `other joint owners, and any manager or trustee exercising powers of management over an ancient`
  line `monument, and the successor in title of any such owner and the successor in office of any such manager`
  line `or trustee:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this Act shall be deemed to extend the powers which may lawfully be`
  line `exercised by such manager or trustee.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O.1937, for "the Govt.".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "the L.G.".`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34773)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Protected monuments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34773&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Central Government] may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `declare an ancient monument to be a protected monument within the meaning of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification published under sub-section (1) shall be fixed up in a conspicuous place`
  line `on or near the monument, together with an intimation that any objections to the issue of the notification`
  line `received by the ^1[Central Government] within one month from the date when it is so fixed up will be taken`
  line `into consideration.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiry of the said period of one month, the ^1[Central Government], after considering the`
  line `objections, if any, shall confirm or withdraw the notification.`
  line
  line `(4) A notification published under this section shall, unless and until it is withdrawn, be conclusive`
  line `evidence of the fact that the monument to which it relates is an ancient monument within the meaning of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34774)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Acquisition of rights in or guardianship of an ancient monument.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G."`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34774&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Collector, with the`
  line `sanction of the ^1[Central Government], may purchase or take a lease of any protected monument.`
  line
  line `(2) The Collector, with the like sanction, may accept a gift or bequest of any protected monument.`
  line
  line `(3) The owner of any protected monument may, by written instrument, constitute the Commissioner the`
  line `guardian of the monument, and the Commissioner may, with the sanction of the ^1[Central Government],`
  line `accept such guardianship.`
  line
  line `(4) When the Commissioner has accepted the guardianship of a monument under sub-section (3), the`
  line `owner shall, except as expressly provided in this Act, have the same estate, right, title and interest in and to`
  line `the monument as if the Commissioner had not been constituted guardian thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) When the Commissioner has accepted the guardianship of a monument under sub-section (3), the`
  line `provisions of this Act relating to agreements executed under section 5 shall apply to the written instrument`
  line `executed under the said sub-section.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a protected monument is without an owner, the Commissioner may assume the guardianship of`
  line `the monument.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34775)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Preservation of ancient monument by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34775&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Collector may, with the previous`
  line `sanction of ^1[the Central Government], propose to the owner to enter into an agreement with ^2[the Central`
  line `Governmen] for the preservation of any protected monument in his district.`
  line
  line `(2) An agreement under this section may provide for the following matters, or for such of them as it may`
  line `be found expedient to include m the agreement:--`
  line
  line `(a) the maintenance of the monument;`
  line
  line `(b) the custody of the monument, and the duties of any person who may be employed to watch it;`
  line
  line `(c) the restriction of the owners right to destroy, remove, alter or deface the monument or to build on`
  line `or near the site of the monument;`
  line
  line `(d) the facilities of access to be permitted to the public or to any portion of the public and to persons`
  line `deputed by the owner or the Collector to inspect or maintain the monument;`
  line
  line `(e) the notice to be given to the Central Government in case the land on which the monument is`
  line `situated is offered for sale by the owner, and the right to be reserved to ^3[the Central Government] to`
  line `purchase such land, or any specified portion of such land, at its market-value;`
  line
  line `(f) the payment of any expenses incurred by the owner or by ^3[the Central Government] in connection`
  line `with the preservation of the monument;`
  line
  line `(g) the proprietary or other rights which are to vest in Government in respect of the monument when`
  line `any expenses reinsured by ^9`
  line `the Central Government in connection with the preservation of the`
  line monument;
  line
  line `(h) the appointment of an authority to decide any dispute arising out of the agreement; and`
  line
  line `(i) any matter connected with the preservation of the monument which is a proper subject of`
  line `agreement between the owner and ^3[the Central Government].`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(4) The terms of an agreement under this section may be altered from time to time with the sanction of`
  line `^5[the Central Government] and with the consent of the owner.`
  line
  line `(5) With the previous sanction of ^5[the Central Government], the Collector may terminate an agreement`
  line `under this section on giving six months notice in writing to the owner.`
  line
  line `(6) The owner may terminate an agreement under this section on giving six months notice to the`
  line Collector.
  line
  line `(7) An agreement under this section shall be binding on any person claiming to be owner of the`
  line `monument to which it relates, through or under a party by whom or on whose behalf the agreement was`
  line executed.
  line
  line `(8) Any rights acquired by ^3[the Central Government] in respect of expenses incurred in protecting or`
  line `preserving a monument shall not be affected by the termination of an agreement under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs., ibid., for "the L.G".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "the Secretary of State for India in council".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O.1937, for "the Government".`
  line
  line `4. Sub-section (3) omitted, ibid.`
  line
  line `5. Subs., ibid., for "the L.G"..`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (34776)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Owners under disability or not in possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34776&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the owner is unable, by reason of infancy or`
  line `other disability, to act for himself, the person legally competent to act on his behalf may exercise the powers`
  line `conferred upon an owner by section 5.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of village-property, the headman or other village-officer exercising powers of management`
  line `over such property may exercise the powers conferred upon an owner by section 5.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to empower any person not being of the same religion as the`
  line `persons on whose behalf he is acting to make or execute an agreement relating to a protected monument`
  line `which or any part of which is periodically used for the religious worship or observances of that religion.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (34777)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Enforcement of agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34777&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Collector apprehends that the owner or occupier of a`
  line `monument intends to destroy, remove, alter, deface, or imperil the monument or to build on or near the site`
  line `thereof in contravention of the terms of an agreement for its preservation under section 5, the Collector may`
  line `make an order prohibiting any such contravention of the agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) If an owner or other person who is bound by an agreement for the preservation or maintenance of a`
  line `monument under section 5 refuses to do any act which is in the opinion of the Collector necessary to such`
  line `preservation or maintenance, or neglects to do any such act within such reasonable time as may be fixed by`
  line `the Collector, the Collector may authorize any person to do any such act, and the expense of doing any such`
  line `act or such portion of the expense as the owner may be liable to pay under the agreement may be recovered`
  line `from the owner as if it were an arrear of land-revenue.`
  line
  line `(3) A person aggrieved by an order made under this section may appeal to the Commissioner, who may`
  line `cancel or modify it and whose decision shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (34798)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Purchasers at certain sales and persons claiming through owner bound by instrument executed by owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34798&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Every person who purchases, at a sale for arrears of land-revenue or any other public demand, or`
  line `at a sale made under the Bengal Patni Taluks Regulation, 1819, (Ben. Reg. 8 of 1819) an estate or tenure in`
  line `which is situated a monument in respect of which any instrument has been executed by the owner for the time`
  line `being, under section 4 or section 5 and every person claiming any title to a monument from, through or under`
  line `an owner who executed any such instrument, shall be bound by such instrument.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (34779)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Application of endowment to repair of an ancient monument.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34779&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any owner or other person`
  line `competent to enter into an agreement under section 5 for the preservation of a protected monument, refuses or`
  line `fails to enter into such an agreement when proposed to him by the Collector, and if any endowment has been`
  line `created for the purpose of keeping such monument in repair, or for that purpose among others, the Collector`
  line `may institute a suit in the Court of the District Judge, or, if the estimated cost of repairing the monument does`
  line `not exceed one thousand rupees, may make an application to the District Judge for the proper application of`
  line `such endowment or part thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) On the hearing of an application under sub-section (1), the District Judge may summon and examine`
  line `the owner and any person whose evidence appears to him necessary, and may pass an order for the proper`
  line `application of the endowment or of any part thereof, and any such order may be executed as if it were the`
  line `decree of a Civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (34799)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Compulsory purchase of ancient monument.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34799&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the ^1[Central Government] apprehends that a`
  line `protected monument is in danger of being destroyed, injured or allowed to fall into decay ^2[the Central`
  line `Government may direct the State Government to acquire it] under the provisions of the Land Acquisition`
  line `Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), as if the preservation of a protected monument were a "public purpose" within the`
  line `meaning of that Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The powers of compulsory purchase conferred by sub-section (1) shall not be exercised in the case`
  line of--
  line
  line `(a) any monument which or any part of which is periodically used for religious observances; or`
  line
  line `(b) any monument which is the subject of a subsisting agreement executed under section 5.`
  line
  line `(3) In any case other than the cases referred to in sub-section (2) the said powers of compulsory purchase`
  line `shall not be exercised unless the owner or other person competent to enter into an agreement under section 5`
  line `has failed, within such reasonable period as the Collector may fix in this behalf, to enter into an agreement`
  line `proposed to him under the said section or has terminated or given notice of his intention to terminate such an`
  line agreement.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O.1937, for "L.G.".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "the L.G. may proceed to acquire it".`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (38027)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Power Central Government to control mining, etc., near ancient monument.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=38027&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Power Central Government to control mining, etc., near ancient monument--(1) If the^2[Central Government] is of opinion that mining, quarrying, excavating, blasting and other operations of a`
  line `like nature should be restricted or regulated for the purpose of protecting, or preserving any ancient`
  line `monument, the ^2[Central Government] may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules--`
  line
  line `(a) fixing the boundaries of the area to which the rules are to apply,`
  line
  line `(b) forbidding the carrying on of mining, quarrying, excavating, blasting or any operation of a like`
  line `nature except in accordance with the rules and with the terms of a licence, and`
  line
  line `(c) prescribing the authority by which, and the terms on which, licences may be granted to carry on`
  line `any of the said operations.`
  line
  line `(2) The power to make rules given by this section is subject to the condition of the rules being made after`
  line `previous publication.`
  line
  line `(3) A rule made under this section may provide that any person committing a breach thereof shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) If any owner or occupier of land included in a notification under sub-section (1) proves to the`
  line `satisfaction of the ^2[Central Government] that he has sustained loss by reason of such land being so included,`
  line `the ^2[Central Government shall pay compensation in respect of such loss.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 1932, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O.1937, for "L.G.".`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (34781)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Maintenance of certain protected monuments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34781&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner shall maintain every`
  line `monument in respect of which the Government has acquired any of the rights mentioned in section 4 or which`
  line `the Government has acquired under section 10.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Commissioner has accepted the guardianship of a monument under section 4, he shall, for`
  line `the purpose of maintaining such monument, have access to the monument at all reasonable times, by himself`
  line `and by his agents, subordinates and workmen, for the purpose of inspecting the monument, and for the`
  line `purpose of bringing such materials and doing such acts as he may consider necessary or desirable for the`
  line `maintenance thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (34782)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Voluntary contributions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34782&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner may receive voluntary contributions towards the cost`
  line `of maintaining a protected monument and may give orders as to the management and application of any funds`
  line `so received by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that no contribution received under this section shall he applied to any purpose other than the`
  line `purpose for which it was contributed.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (34783)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Protection of place of worship from misuse, pollution or desecration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34783&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) A place of worship or`
  line `shrine maintained by the Government under this Act shall not be used for any purpose inconsistent with its`
  line character.
  line
  line `(2) Where the Collector has, under section 4, purchased or taken a lease of any protected monument, or`
  line `has accepted a gift or bequest, or the Commissioner has, under the same section, accepted the guardianship`
  line `thereof, and such monument, or any part thereof, is periodically used for religious worship or observances by`
  line `any community, the Collector shall make due provision for the protection of such monument or such part`
  line `thereof, from pollution or desecration--`
  line
  line `(a) by prohibiting the entry therein, except n accordance with conditions prescribed with the`
  line `concurrence of the persons in religious charge of the said monument or part thereof, of any person not`
  line `entitled so to enter by the religious usages of the community by which the monument or part thereof is`
  line `used, or`
  line
  line `(b) by taking such other action as he may think necessary in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (34784)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Relinquishment of Government rights in a monument.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34784&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `With the sanction of ^1[the Central`
  line `Government], the Commissioner may--`
  line
  line `(a) where rights have been acquired by ^2[the Central Government] in respect of any monument`
  line `under this Act by virtue of any sale, lease, gift or will, relinquish the rights so acquired to the person who`
  line `would for the time being be the owner of the monument if such rights had not been acquired; or`
  line
  line `(b) relinquish any guardianship of a monument which he has accepted under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O.1937, for "the L.G.".`
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "Govt.".`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (34785)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Right of access to certain protected monuments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34785&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such rules as may after previous`
  line `publication be made by ^2[the Central Government], the public shall have a nut right of access to any`
  line `monument maintained by ^2[the Central Government] under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In making any rule under sub-section (1) ^1[the Central Government] may provide that a breach of it`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to twenty rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O.1937, for "the L.G.".`
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "Govt.".`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (34786)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs., ibid., for "Govt.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34786&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Any person other than the owner who destroys, removes, injures, alters, defaces or`
  line `imperils a protected monument, and any owner who destroys, removes, injures, alters, defaces or imperils a`
  line `monument maintained by ^1[the Central Government] under this Act or in respect of which an agreement has`
  line `been executed under section 5, and any owner or occupier who contravenes an order made under section 7,`
  line `sub-section (1), shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to three months, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (34787)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to Central Government to control traffic in antiquities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34787&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government`
  line `apprehends that antiquities that are being sold or removed to the detriment of India or of any neighbouring`
  line `country, it may, by notification^1`
  line `in the Official Gazette, prohibit or restrict the bringing or taking by sea or by`
  line `land of any antiquities or class of antiquities described in the notification into or out of ^2[the territories to`
  line `which this Act extends] or any specified part of ^3[the said territories].`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who brings or takes or attempts to bring or take any such antiquities into or out of ^3[the`
  line `said territories] or any part of ^3[the said territories] in contravention of a notification issued under sub-section`
  line `(1), shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Antiquities in respect of which an offence referred to in sub-section (2) has been committed shall be`
  line `liable to confiscation.`
  line
  line `(4) An officer of Customs, or an officer of Police of a grade not lower than Sub-Inspector, duly`
  line `empowered by the ^4[Central Government] in this behalf, may search any vessel, cart or other means of`
  line `conveyance, and may open any baggage or package of goods, if he has reason to believe that goods in respect`
  line `of which an offence has been committed under sub-section (2) are contained therein.`
  line
  line `(5) A person who complains that the power of search mentioned in sub-section (4) has been vexatiously`
  line `or improperly exercised may address his complaint to the ^4[Central Government], and the ^4[Central`
  line `Governmen] shall pass such order and may award such compensation, if any, as appears to it to be just.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. For notification, see Gazette of India, 1917, Pt. I, p. 989.`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and "the Schedule, for the territories for the time being comprised within Part A States and Part C`
  line `States".`
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "the Provinces".`
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L. G"..`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (34788)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power to Central Government to control moving of sculptures , carvings or like objects.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34788&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) If^1[the Central Government] considers that any sculptures, carvings, images, bas-reliefs, inscriptions or other`
  line `like objects ought not to be moved from the place where they are without the sanction of ^2[the CentralGovernment], ^1[the Central Government] may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any such`
  line `object or any class of such objects shall not be moved unless with the written permission of the Collector.`
  line
  line `(2) A person applying for the permission mentioned in sub-section (1) shall specify the object or objects`
  line `which he proposes to move and shall furnish, in regard to such object or objects, any information which the`
  line `Collector may require.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Collector refuses to grant such permission, the applicant may appeal to the Commissioner,`
  line `whose decision shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who moves any object in contravention of a notification issued under sub-section (1),`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(5) If the owner of any property proves to the satisfaction of ^1[the Central Government] that he has`
  line `suffered any loss or damage by reason of the inclusion of such property in a notification published under subsection (1), ^1[the Central Government] shall either--`
  line
  line `(a) exempt such property from the said notification;`
  line
  line `(b) purchase such property, if it be moveable, at its market - value; or`
  line
  line `(c) pay compensation for any loss or damage sustained by the owner of such property, if it be`
  line immoveable.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the L.G".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "the Govt.".`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (34789)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Purchase of sculptures, carvings or like objects by the Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34789&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) If ^1[the CentralGovernmen] apprehends that any object mentioned in a notification issued under section 18,`
  line `sub-section (1), is in danger of being destroyed, removed, injured or allowed to fall into decay, ^1[the CentralGovernment] may pass orders for the compulsory purchase of such object at its market-value, and the`
  line `Collector shall thereupon give notice to the owner of the object to be purchased.`
  line
  line `(2) The power of compulsory purchase given by this section shall not extend to--`
  line
  line `(a) any image or symbol actually used for the purpose of any religious observance; or`
  line
  line `(b) anything which the owner desires to retain on any reasonable ground personal to himself or to`
  line `any of his ancestors or to any member of his family.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (34790)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power of Central Government to notify areas as protected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. The words "after consulting the L.G." omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34790&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government ^1***`
  line `is of opinion that excavation for archeological purposes in any area should be restricted and regulated in the`
  line `interests of archeological research, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette`
  line `specifying the boundaries of the area, declare it to be a protected area.`
  line
  line `(2) From the date of such notification all antiquities buried in the protected area shall be the property of`
  line `the Government and shall be deemed to be in the possession of the Government, and shall remain the`
  line `property and in the possession of the Government until Ownership thereof is transferred; but in all other`
  line `respects the rights of any owner or occupier of land in such area shall not be affected.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_a:
  sectionId (34791)
  sectionNo 20A
  orderNo 22
  title `Power to enter upon and make excavations in a protected area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the Govt.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34791&sectionno=20A&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any officer of the`
  line `Archeological Department or any person holding a licence under section 20B may, with the`
  line `written permission of the Collector enter upon and make excavations in any, protected area.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, in the exercise of the power conferred by sub-section (1), the rights of any person are`
  line `infringed by the occupation or disturbance of the surface of any land, ^1[the Central Government] shall pay to`
  line `that person compensation for the infringement.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_b:
  sectionId (34800)
  sectionNo 20B
  orderNo 23
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules regulating Archaeological excavation in protected areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34800&sectionno=20B&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_20_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may make rules^2--`
  line
  line `(a) prescribing the authorities by whom licences to excavate for archeological purposes in a`
  line `protected area may be granted;`
  line
  line `(b) regulating the conditions on which such licences may be granted, the form of such licences, and`
  line `the taking of security from licensees;`
  line
  line `(c) prescribing the manner in which antiquities found by a licensee shall be divided between ^1[the`
  line `Central Government] and the licensee; and`
  line
  line `(d) generally to carry out the purposes of section 20.`
  line
  line `(2) The power to make rules given by this section is subject to the condition of the rules being made after`
  line `previous publication.`
  line
  line `(3) Such rules may be general for all protected areas for the time being, or may be special for any`
  line `particular protected area or areas.`
  line
  line `(4) Such rules may provide that any person committing a breach of any rule or of any condition of a`
  line `licence shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, and may further provide that`
  line `where the breach has been by the agent or servant of a licensee the licensee himself shall be punishable.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the Govt.".`
  line
  line `2. For such rules, see Gazette of India, 1934, Pt. I, p. 1103.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_c:
  sectionId (34793)
  sectionNo 20C
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to acquire a protected area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34793&sectionno=20C&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_20_c_content:
  string
  line `If the Central Government is of opinion that a protected area`
  line `contains an ancient monument or antiquities of national interest and value, it may direct the State`
  line `Government to acquire such area, or any part thereof, and the State Government may thereupon acquire such`
  line `area or part under the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), as for a public purpose.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (34794)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 25
  title `Assessment of market-value or compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34794&sectionno=21&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The market-value of any property which`
  line `Government is empowered to purchase at such value under this Act, or the ^1*** compensation to be paid by`
  line `Government in respect of anything done under this Act, shall, where any dispute arises ^2[in respect] of such`
  line `market-value or compensation, be ascertained in the manner provided by the Land Acquisition Act, 1894,`
  line `sections 3, 8 to 34, 45 to 47, 51and 52, so far as they can be made applicable:`
  line
  line `Provided that when making an inquiry under the said Land Acquisition Act, 1894, the Collector shall be`
  line `assisted by two assessors' one of whom shall be a competent person nominated by the Collector, and one a`
  line `person nominated by the owner or, in case the owner fails to nominate an assessor within such reasonable`
  line `time as may be fixed by the Collector in this behalf, by the Collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "amount of" omitted by Act 18 of 1932, s. 4.`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "touching the amount".`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (34795)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 26
  title Jurisdiction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34795&sectionno=22&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `A Magistrate of the third class shall not have jurisdiction to try any person charged`
  line `with an offence against this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (34796)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or the L.G." omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34796&sectionno=23&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government ^1*** may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules for carrying out any of the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The power to make rules given by this section is subject to the condition of the rules being made after`
  line `previous publication.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (34797)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 28
  title `Protection to public servants acting under Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367&sectionId=34797&sectionno=24&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_0_00013_190407_1523340103367
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `No suit for compensation and no criminal`
  line `proceeding shall lie against any public servant in respect of any act done, or in good faith intended to be done,`
  line `in the exercise of any power conferred by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
